P\left[X+Y>\frac{1}{2}\right]=\int\int f\left(x,y\right)dxdy=\int_{0}^{1}\int_{\frac{1}{2}-y}^{1}f\left(x,y\right)dxdy
y\leq\frac{1}{2}
\int_{\frac{1}{2}-y}^{1}f\left(x,y\right)dx=\int_{\frac{1}{2}-y}^{1}dx=y+\frac{1}{2}
y>\frac{1}{2}
\int_{\frac{1}{2}-y}^{1}f\left(x,y\right)dx=\int_{0}^{1}f\left(x,y\right)dx+\int_{\frac{1}{2}-y}^{0}f\left(x,y\right)dx=\int_{0}^{1}dx+\int_{\frac{1}{2}-y}^{0}0dx=1
P\left[X+Y>\frac{1}{2}\right]=\int_{0}^{\frac{1}{2}}\left(y+\frac{1}{2}\right)dy+\int_{\frac{1}{2}}^{1}1dy=\frac{3}{8}+\frac{1}{2}=\frac{7}{8}
